      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:22:3",
      "text": [
        " الرَّجُلِ يَقْتُلُ مَمْلُوكاً لَهُ قَالَ يُعْتِقُ رَقَبَةً وَ يَصُومُ شَهْرَيْنِ مُتَتَابِعَيْنِ وَ يَتُوبُ إِلَى اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abu Ayoub, from Humran, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> regarding the man who kills a slave of his. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He has to emancipate a neck, and Fast for two months consecutively, and repents to Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic’."
        ]
      }
    },
